---
alwaysApply: true
---

Apply to all implementation work without exception:

- Tests are written alongside code, never after.
- Every function gets at minimum: one happy path test, one edge case 
  test, one failure case test.
- Test names describe behavior, not implementation. 
  "returns empty list when no results found" not "test_query_fn".
- No task is marked done until its tests pass.
- For any function with complex logic, write the tests before the 
  implementation.
- Never mock what you can test directly.
- If a bug is fixed, a regression test is added before closing 
  the task.
- If a task is marked [REVISIT] due to a change, existing tests 
  for that task must be reviewed and updated before it is 
  re-approved.
- Never merge a branch that has failing tests.
